fields.name: name
fields.description: The friendly name of the API Key

fields.name: key_value
fields.description: key_value is only returned on initial creation or when it is regenerated
fields.label: optional

fields.name: expires_at
fields.description: The timestamp of what the API key expires and will not longer be usable.

fields.name: expires_at
fields.description: Validate between now and one year: now < x < 365 days

fields.name: expires_at
fields.description: Validate between now and one year: now < x < 365 days

services.name: ApiKeyService
services.description: Service that manages the lifecycle of API Keys that are associated with a specific Account.

methods.name: GetAccountApiKeys
methods.description: Retrieves a list of Account API Keys

methods.name: GetAccountApiKey
methods.description: Retrieves a single API Key

methods.name: CreateAccountApiKey
methods.description:
Creates a single API Key
This method will return the decrypted contents of the API key

methods.name: RegenerateAccountApiKey
methods.description:
Regenerates a single API Key with a new expiration time
This method will return the decrypted contents of the API key

methods.name: DeleteAccountApiKey
methods.description: Deletes an API Key from the system.

messages.name: AccessToken
messages.description: A decoded representation of an Access token from the backing auth server

fields.name: access_token
fields.description: The access token that will be provided in subsequent requests to provide authenticated access to the Api

fields.name: refresh_token
fields.description:
Token that can be used to retrieve a refreshed access token.
Will not be provided if the offline_access scope is not provided in the initial login flow.
fields.label: optional

fields.name: expires_in
fields.description: Relative time in seconds that the access token will expire. Combine with the current time to get the expires_at time.

fields.name: scope
fields.description: The scopes that the access token have

fields.name: id_token
fields.description: The identity token of the authenticated user
fields.label: optional

fields.name: token_type
fields.description: The token type. For JWTs, this will be `Bearer`

fields.name: is_enabled
fields.description:
Whether or not the server has authentication enabled.
This tells the client if it is expected to send access tokens.

fields.name: state
fields.description: The state that's generated by the client that is passed along to prevent tampering

fields.name: redirect_uri
fields.description: The redirect uri that the client will be redirected back to during the auth request

fields.name: scope
fields.description: The scopes the client is requesting as a part of the oauth login request

fields.name: url
fields.description: The generated url that is the client will be redirected to during the Oauth flow

fields.name: issuer_url
fields.description: The backing authentication issuer url

fields.name: audience
fields.description: The audience that will be used in the access token. This corresponds to the "aud" claim

fields.name: code
fields.description: The oauth code

fields.name: redirect_uri
fields.description: The oauth redirect uri that the client uses during the oauth request

fields.name: access_token
fields.description: The access token that is returned on successful login

fields.name: refresh_token
fields.description: The token used to retrieve a new access token.

fields.name: access_token
fields.description: The access token that is returned on successful refresh

services.name: AuthService
services.description:
Service that handles generic Authentication for Neosync
Today this is mostly used by the CLI to receive authentication information

methods.name: LoginCli
methods.description: Used by the CLI to login to Neosync with OAuth.

methods.name: RefreshCli
methods.description:
Used by the CLI to refresh an expired Neosync accesss token.
This should only be used if an access token was previously retrieved from the `LoginCli` or `RefreshCli` methods.

methods.name: CheckToken
methods.description: Empty endpoint to simply check if the provided access token is valid

methods.name: GetCliIssuer
methods.description:
Used by the CLI to retrieve Auth Issuer information
@deprecated

methods.name: GetAuthorizeUrl
methods.description: Used by the CLI to retrieve an Authorize URL for use with OAuth login.

methods.name: GetAuthStatus
methods.description:
Returns the auth status of the API server. Whether or not the backend has authentication enabled.
This is used by clients to make decisions on whether or not they should send access tokens to the API.

messages.name: AwsS3Credentials
messages.description:
S3 Credentials that are used by the worker process.
Note: this may be optionally provided if the worker that is being hosted has environment credentials to the S3 bucket instead.

fields.name: is_connected
fields.description: Whether or not the API was able to ping the connection

fields.name: connection_error
fields.description: This is the error that was received if the API was unable to connect
fields.label: optional

fields.name: id
fields.description: The connection id that the query will be checked against

fields.name: query
fields.description: The full query that will be run through a PREPARE statement

fields.name: is_valid
fields.description: The query is run through PREPARE. Returns valid if it correctly compiled

fields.name: erorr_message
fields.description: The error message returned by the sql client if the prepare did not return successfully
fields.label: optional

fields.name: name
fields.description: The friendly name of the connection

services.name: ConnectionService
services.description:
Service for managing datasource connections.
This is a primary data model in Neosync and is used in reference when hooking up Jobs to synchronize and generate data.

methods.name: GetConnections
methods.description: Returns a list of connections associated with the account

methods.name: GetConnection
methods.description: Returns a single connection

methods.name: CreateConnection
methods.description: Creates a new connection

methods.name: UpdateConnection
methods.description: Updates an existing connection

methods.name: DeleteConnection
methods.description: Removes a connection from the system.

methods.name: IsConnectionNameAvailable
methods.description: Connections have friendly names, this method checks if the requested name is available in the system based on the account

methods.name: CheckConnectionConfig
methods.description:
Checks if the connection config is connectable by the backend.
Used mostly to verify that a connection is valid prior to creating a Connection object.

methods.name: CheckSqlQuery
methods.description:
Checks a constructed SQL query against a sql-based connection to see if it's valid based on that connection's data schema
This is useful when constructing subsets to see if the WHERE clause is correct

fields.name: schema
fields.description: The database schema. Ex: public

fields.name: table
fields.description: The name of the table in the schema

fields.name: column
fields.description: The name of the column

fields.name: data_type
fields.description: The datatype of the column

messages.name: GetConnectionDataStreamResponse
messages.description: Each stream response is a single row in the requested schema and table

fields.name: row
fields.description: A map of column name to the bytes value of the data that was found for that column and row
fields.label: repeated

messages.name: GetConnectionForeignConstraintsResponse
messages.description: Dependency constraints for a specific table

fields.name: table_constraints
fields.description: the key here is <schema>.<table> and the list of tables that it depends on, also `<schema>.<table>` format.
fields.label: repeated

messages.name: GetConnectionInitStatementsResponse
messages.description: Init statement for a specific table

fields.name: table_init_statements
fields.description: the key here is <schema>.<table> and value is the table init statement.
fields.label: repeated

services.name: ConnectionDataService
services.description:
Service for managing connection data.
This is used in handle data from a connection

methods.name: GetConnectionDataStream
methods.description:
Streaming endpoint that will stream the data available from the Connection to the client.
Used primarily by the CLI sync command.

methods.name: GetConnectionSchema
methods.description: Returns the schema for a specific connection. Used mostly for SQL-based connections

methods.name: GetConnectionForeignConstraints
methods.description:
For a specific connection, returns the foreign key constraints. Mostly useful for SQL-based Connections.
Used primarily by the CLI sync command to determine stream order.

methods.name: GetConnectionInitStatements
methods.description:
For a specific connection, returns the init table statements. Mostly useful for SQL-based Connections.
Used primarily by the CLI sync command to create table schema init statement.

scalarValueTypes.notes: Uses variable-length encoding. Inefficient for encoding negative numbers  if your field is likely to have negative values, use sint32 instead.
Uses variable-length encoding. Inefficient for encoding negative numbers  if your field is likely to have negative values, use sint64 instead.
Uses variable-length encoding. Signed int value. These more efficiently encode negative numbers than regular int32s.
Uses variable-length encoding. Signed int value. These more efficiently encode negative numbers than regular int64s.
Always four bytes. More efficient than uint32 if values are often greater than 2^28.
Always eight bytes. More efficient than uint64 if values are often greater than 2^56.
A string must always contain UTF-8 encoded or 7-bit ASCII text.
May contain any arbitrary sequence of bytes.
